<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 3:09PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Gordon
and northwestern Bartow Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 309 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Sonoraville, or near
Calhoun, moving southeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Calhoun, Adairsville, Sonoraville, Folsom and Funkhouser.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
